<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Defs>

  <!--
    Better Traders Guild - Bounded Defender Duty

    BTG_DefendStructure: Combat-engaged defensive posture that never assaults.
    Pawns with this duty, in priority order:
    1. Acquire and engage hostile targets, but only inside the settlement
       structure (target acquisition filtered by JobGiver_BTGDefendStructure).
       Combat is first, so a defender never breaks off to eat/tend while a
       valid in-structure target remains.
    2. When no target remains: self-tend wounds, then eat when hungry. Both are
       wrapped in ThinkNode_ForbidOutsideFlagRadius, which marks every cell more
       than maxDistToSquadFlag from the duty focus (baseCenter) as forbidden for
       the duration of the wrapped subtree. JobGiver_GetFood therefore cannot
       path to food outside the structure footprint. (Mirrors how vanilla
       DefendBase / Defend wrap SatisfyBasicNeeds; matches the 16-cell radius
       vanilla uses for entrenched defenders.) JobGiver_SelfTend tends in place,
       so the wrap never affects it, but it stays inside for parity.
    3. Fall back to wandering near the focus point (radius 12) when idle.

    Containment summary — defenders never leave the structure because:
      * combat targets are filtered to the union of room rects, and
        JobGiver_AIDefendPoint (chaseTarget=false) holds firing positions within
        the duty radius of baseCenter rather than pursuing, and
      * need-satisfaction is leashed to maxDistToSquadFlag of baseCenter.

    Used by: LordJob_BTGDefendStructure, assigned to settlement defenders
    (gestator-spawned mechs and, in future, human guards). Self-tend and
    GetFood are inert for mechs (SelfTend is Humanlike-gated; mechs have no food
    need) and take effect only once human guards join this lord.

    Design intent: model a "reverse siege" where defenders hold an entrenched,
    terrain-advantaged position and never path out of the structure to chase
    intruders or forage.
  -->

  <DutyDef>
    <defName>BTG_DefendStructure</defName>
    <thinkNode Class="ThinkNode_Priority">
      <subNodes>
        <!-- 1. Combat first: engage in-structure targets before any need. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGDefendStructure" />
        <!-- 2. Needs, leashed near baseCenter so foragers never leave the structure. -->
        <li Class="ThinkNode_ForbidOutsideFlagRadius">
          <maxDistToSquadFlag>16</maxDistToSquadFlag>
          <subNodes>
            <li Class="JobGiver_SelfTend" />
            <li Class="JobGiver_GetFood">
              <minCategory>Hungry</minCategory>
            </li>
          </subNodes>
        </li>
        <!-- 3. Idle: wander near the focus point. -->
        <li Class="JobGiver_WanderNearDutyLocation">
          <wanderRadius>12</wanderRadius>
        </li>
      </subNodes>
    </thinkNode>
  </DutyDef>

</Defs>
